claim.claim-text:
A display device (100) comprising:
a gate line (GL) positioned in a first direction on a substrate to transfer a gate signal;
a data line (DL) positioned in a second direction on the substrate to transfer a data signal;
a thin film transistor positioned at each pixel defined by a crossing of the gate line (GL) and the data line (DL);
a first electrode (840a) spaced from one of a source electrode (824) or a drain electrode (826) of the thin film transistor;
a second electrode (870a) facing the first electrode (840a);
a thin film transistor protective layer positioned on the thin film transistor and has a first contact hole formed therein;
a touch signal line positioned between a first touch connection pattern (840b), which is made of a same material as that of the first electrode (840a) to be separated from the first electrode (840a), and a second touch connection pattern (870b), which is made of a same material as that of the second electrode (870a) to be connected with the second electrode (870a), and transfers a touch driving signal to the second touch connection pattern (870b);
a first connection pattern made of the same material as that of the second electrode (870a) and connects the source electrode (824) or the drain electrode (826) with the first electrode (840a) through the first contact hole; and
a first electrode protective layer (860) positioned on the first electrode (840a) and the touch signal line.
